cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as keyphrase extraction from documents. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as keyphrase extraction is useful for information retrieval applications. Additionally, the use of graph convolutional networks and neural network-based approaches suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the proposed diversified point network for generating diverse keyphrases could also suggest a potential fit for cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
